  "body": "<!-- Please only use this template for submitting enhancement requests -->\r\n\r\n**What would you like to be added**:\r\nCurrently test names are formed by concatenating the ginkgo context's together. The testname is used to create a directory. This creates a limit on the length of the the testname, as most operating systems can only support a filename of up to 255 bytes. This concatenating is done by the logging library (I think)\r\n\r\nA way to break up the long test names by ginkgo context.\r\n**Why is this needed**:\r\nThis test (https://prow.k8s.io/view/gcs/kubernetes-jenkins/pr-logs/pull/92555/pull-kubernetes-e2e-gce-storage-snapshot/1277695556403073024/) failed on PR #92555 \r\n\r\nCurrent workarounds are simple by shortening the test names. However this is not desirable if we wish to support more nesting of ginkgo contexts in order to reduce boilerplate testing code by sharing common setup. This is also not desirable because it limits the ability to communicate the intent of the .",
